Kremlin allies falsely claim that Aiden Aslin, 28, originally from Newark in Nottinghamshire and Shaun Pinner, 48, from Bedfordshire are foreign mercenaries.  The Foreign Secretary had talks with Ukrainian foreign minister Dmytro Kuleba amid suggestions a prisoner swap could be negotiated. Ms Truss told BBC Radio 4: "I will do whatever is necessary." She did not rule out negotiating directly with the self-proclaimed Donetsk People's Republic. 